@startuml
title Cloud Food Corner - Current Request Flow

actor Customer
participant "Browser" as Browser
participant "HomeController" as HomeController
participant "MenuController" as MenuController
participant "OrderController" as OrderController
participant "MenuService" as MenuService
collections "In-memory Menu List" as MenuList
entity "Category enum" as Category
entity "Order model" as Order
participant "Thymeleaf home.html" as HomeView
participant "Thymeleaf menu.html" as MenuView
participant "Thymeleaf orderForm.html" as OrderFormView

== Home Page ==
Customer -> Browser : Open application
Browser -> HomeController : GET /api
HomeController -> HomeView : return "home"
HomeView --> Browser : Render homepage
Browser --> Customer : Show home page

== Menu Page ==
Customer -> Browser : Open menu
Browser -> MenuController : GET /api/menu
MenuController -> MenuService : getAllItems()
MenuService -> MenuList : Build in-memory List<MenuItem>
MenuList --> MenuService : menuItems
MenuService --> MenuController : menuItems
MenuController -> MenuService : getByCategory(MAIN_COURSE)
MenuService -> MenuList : filter by category
MenuList --> MenuService : mainCourse
MenuService --> MenuController : mainCourse
MenuController -> MenuService : getByCategory(STREET_FOOD)
MenuService -> MenuList : filter by category
MenuList --> MenuService : streetFood
MenuService --> MenuController : streetFood
MenuController -> MenuService : getByCategory(SWEETS)
MenuService -> MenuList : filter by category
MenuList --> MenuService : sweets
MenuService --> MenuController : sweets
MenuController -> MenuService : getByCategory(BEVERAGES)
MenuService -> MenuList : filter by category
MenuList --> MenuService : beverages
MenuService --> MenuController : beverages
MenuController -> Category : Read category values

note right of MenuController
Adds model attributes:
- menuItems
- mainCourse
- streetFood
- sweets
- beverages
- categories
end note

MenuController -> MenuView : return "menu" with model
MenuView --> Browser : Render categorized menu
Browser --> Customer : Show menu page

== Order Form ==
Customer -> Browser : Click "Place Order"
Browser -> OrderController : GET /api/order/current
OrderController -> Order : new Order()
OrderController -> OrderFormView : return "orderForm" with order
OrderFormView --> Browser : Render order form
Browser --> Customer : Show order form

== Order Submission ==
Customer -> Browser : Submit order details
Browser -> OrderController : POST /api/order
OrderController -> OrderController : log submitted Order
OrderController --> Browser : redirect:/api
Browser -> HomeController : GET /api
HomeController -> HomeView : return "home"
HomeView --> Browser : Render homepage
Browser --> Customer : Show redirected home page

note bottom
Current state:
- Server-rendered Spring MVC app
- Thymeleaf templates for UI
- Menu data is built in MenuService
- MenuService filters menu items by category in memory
- Order form binds to the Order model
- Submitted orders are logged only
- No database, cart persistence, or payment flow yet
end note

== Future Improvements ==
database "Database" as DB
participant "CartController" as CartController
participant "CheckoutController" as CheckoutController
participant "PaymentController" as PaymentController
participant "Payment Gateway" as PaymentGateway

Browser -> MenuController : GET /api/menu
MenuController -> MenuService : fetch menu from persistence
MenuService -> DB : load menu items
DB --> MenuService : menu items
MenuService --> MenuController : categorized menu
MenuController -> MenuView : return "menu"

Browser -> CartController : POST /api/cart
CartController -> DB : store cart state
DB --> CartController : updated cart
CartController --> Browser : updated cart response/view

Browser -> CheckoutController : POST /api/checkout
CheckoutController -> DB : save order
DB --> CheckoutController : order id / status
CheckoutController -> PaymentController : initiate payment
PaymentController -> PaymentGateway : process payment
PaymentGateway --> PaymentController : payment status
PaymentController --> CheckoutController : payment result
CheckoutController --> Browser : order confirmation

note bottom
Recommended next steps:
- Add persistence with a database and repositories
- Store cart and order state
- Add a checkout flow
- Integrate payment processing
- Add order confirmation and status tracking
- Introduce validation for submitted order data
end note
@enduml
